data.title: Our Favorite place for after dinner
data.text: Our family has gone to Indulge after dinner and ENJOYED their wine and Chocolates!!  People are super friendly and the goodies are Awesome!!

data.title: Excellent Choice of Wines!
data.text: We stopped in for a drink after work one Wednesday evening and it just happened to be Ladies Night.  We were contemplating a "flight" of wine but were concerned that it would be too much wine.  Our server informed us that because it was Ladies Night, the first glass was on him and each glass of wine after that is $5.00.  He basically said that we could have three full glasses of wine in our flight for $10.00.  We decided against a flight.  We did enjoy a couple of glasses of wine, however, and they were very tasty.  The place is small and it was busy.  They do offer some appetizers to go with the wine.  I look forward to returning to Indulge, most likely on a Wednesday evening!

data.title: Private party at Indulge
data.text: Went to a private event there. The same people own Cubanita's and they served delicious Cuban food.  Wonderful wine and desserts too.

data.title: Expected more
data.text:
Our friend had seen reviews of this place and being wine lovers, we thought we'd visit for a glass (bottle) after having dinner downtown. It was a bit unnoticeable from the street - you need the address. 
We really were not impressed. The interior was fine, but not cozy, the wine list was fine, but pricey, and the music was more for a club, not a wine bar.
We will chose to skip this place next time. It was just not what we were looking for.

data.title: Great place for a drink!
data.text: We stopped in and had a drink at Indulge prior to our dinner reservation down the street. It was a calm and great vibe and the staff was so friendly. We just had to experience some of the charcuterie on the menu - which was really tasty. Didn't have the chocolates but they looked amazing!

data.title: Great service
data.text: I went in unaware of the space and what to expect.  I found a great selection and staff. I as requested an items they did not have, the server quickly went next door and acquired it.  I would go back in a heartbeat.

data.title: Outstanding
data.text: My husband brought me to Indulge for a date night and I fell in love all over again! They offer an extensive list of wines from all over the world. I really enjoyed their wine flights. A great way to sample something different. Amazing deserts and cheeses as well. Very knowledgeable staff who can answer any question you may have or suggest great wine parings.

data.title: Marta & Co., they are perfect!
data.text: It's later in the evening, you need a place to chill, with great service, wine, decadent food that serves as the best spoil yourself desserts ... Indulge. Period. Incredible chocolates, wines, cheeses, meats, spicy popcorn blessed by the food Gods, and more ... this is part of the treasure of Indulge. The awesome service, attitude, incredible food, and graciousness is the best part of the evening, explore, experiment ... Indulge. Period.

data.title: Staff was the best part
data.text: The place didn't open until late afternoon, but the manager opened it up for me and my party.  Cupcakes were average and dry, chocolates were imaginative but expensive.  The guy was most knowledgeable, helpful and friendly.

data.title: Chocolate Tort!
data.text: This is a great place to grab a sweet and sit with your sweet! I have a sweet tooth (let's see how many times I can use sweet...j/k) so of course I wanted to stop in and see what kinds of creations they were selling. Creations they are. Truffle oil popcorn...just try it! I've never had anything with truffle oil or truffles on it but this was AMAZING...it's not overpowering at all but it's addicting. The owner of Cubanitas owns this place and because we had hit him up at that restaurant first he gave us free popcorn and told us thanks for stopping in here as well. So sweet of him to do so. There is a gentleman that works here that makes the chocolate tort with homemade whipped cream and my god I HAD to order 2 of them because the first one wasn't enough. I've been here twice and will keep coming back. The atmosphere is chill as well.

data.title: We ate at their satellite site, at the Skylight Music Theatre
data.text: You can never be sure what you're going to get at a theatre bar, but this was a very happy surprise!  They keep their menu simple and very good.  The meals are light--after all, they don't want you falling asleep during a performance!  Try it, you'll like it.

data.title: Love this place
data.text: I found this place just across the street from my hotel. The staff were friendly, welcoming and knowledgeable. I was very impressed with their specials and their recommendations. I visit this place each time I'm in Milwaukee

data.title: Great Place for Drinks w/ Friends
data.text: We decided to go to Indulge b/c we were downtown and wanted dessert but already ate dinner. I had heard great things about Indulge and we were not disappointed. The chocolate fondue was amazing! And our waiter was so nice and kept giving us more potato chips (sounds weird but it was a good combo - sweet/salty). We also had some cupcakes and lots and lots of wine. We will definitely be back to try more from the dessert and cheese menu. One more thing, the decor was really neat looking with the leather walls and built-in wine coolers.

data.title: Great happy hour
data.text:
I was with a small group of colleagues when I ate here. I asked the waiter to choose my wine for me and he did an excellent job. He also forgot which red wine was which when he brought our order out - but he could tell which one was which by smelling them. I was impressed that he was that knowledgeable about the wines. 

They also have themed cheeseboards - of course, we chose the Wisconsin board! 

Their happy hour is excellent - on Tuesday nights it's half price glasses. On Thursday night, it's ladies night and ladies get a free glass of wine.

data.title: Great wine bar!
data.text: Great service, ordered a sample platter of cheeses, nuts, berries and crackers.  I will be visiting Indulge on my next visit!

data.title: Wine & Chocolate with my beautiful wife
data.text: Great wine selection and delicious truffles! If you are looking for a meal you may want to go somewhere else first as they do not have a kitchen and a limited menu. We were here for wine and truffles which were both amazing. We also had the cheesecake that did not taste good and then we saw them unpacking them from what looked like a Sysco box. The bartender was wonderful, polite and very helpful. GREAT service is something you can not teach.

data.title: A Pricey, but Worthwhile Treat
data.text: If you are looking for a great glass of wine (try Neyers Syrah), with nice cheeses and chocolate, than Indulge is a great stop. The interior is beautiful with long tables and sturdy chairs. The metal coat hooks off the backs of the chairs were interesting. The wine list was nice and flights are available. We had the Wisconsin cheese tray, 2 glasses of wine each, and 2 truffles each and our bill was around $100 with tip. Our server was great, very attentive and helpful. I guess I would rather forage for cheese and chocolates on the cheap(er) at the nearby Public Market and enjoy some wine at Wine Thief. Overall, Indulge is a one and done experience.

data.title: Wonderful wine, cupcakes and truffles!
data.text: I went here with a few girlfriends for a night out. The atmosphere is very cozy, contemporary and relaxing. They have an extensive menu including flights of wine, flights paired with truffles and many wines by the glass. They also have many different cheeses as well. We ordered the cupcake trio and shared it. They have different flavors but on the day we came they had red velvet, apple spice and double chocolate. They were wonderful! We also had different flavors of truffles such as banana foster (my favorite!) and milk chocolate caramel. The staff is very knowledgeable and helped us with any questions that we had. I will definitely be going back. The only thing that would be nice is if they maybe had some couches to sit back and relax more. I highly recommend trying this wine bar.

data.title: Awesome gem......don't miss the cupcake trio!!
data.text: Great date night place, cheese plates, great wine selection and truffles, don't miss the cupcake trio though.....I have gone here to get them to go if I am in a hurry!!  Great atmosphere for a fun evening, staff is very knowledgeable and excellent service.  Love this place!!!

data.title: A great place for dessert with your date!
data.text: If you love wine and chocolate this is the place for you. So many choices of bite size treats with wines by the glass - yum!  Try the cupcakes - you won't be disappointed.
